RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1M All Weather Track CR: 70. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000, if for $14,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUPER ELLIE stumbled leaving the start but recovered quickly and tracked the early pace from the inside, was well positioned while saving ground through the backstretch run, inched closer along the far turn, took command in upper stretch and drew to a clear lead at the furlong marker, was a bit green into deep stretch, had the margin cut into by the oncoming runner-up but kept to task late to prove best. UNION HEIRESS broke in a bit and crowded CLICKING at the start, settled two wide into the first turn, was steered three wide into the far turn, mounted a five wide bid into the stretch, was not able to impact the winner in the final sixteenth but finished well and secured the place in the final strides. CLICKING was crowded by a neighboring rival at the start and was away a bit slowly, settled inside to begin, saved all of the ground to the far turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch, rallied in deep stretch and held safely in the end for third. Z INDY LINDY was asked to rate in the early going, pulled on the rider and was keen while between runners into the first turn, raced two wide into the backstretch run and settled while tracking the moderate pace to the half-mile pole, maintained a two wide path into the far turn, chased SUPER ELLIE to mid-stretch, lacked the needed response in the final sixteenth and was outkicked. OOPS AND DOWNS settled three wide into the first turn, was unhurried through the backstretch run and raced two wide into the far turn, swung six wide for the stretch drive and offered a belated rally in the late stages. VHAGAR showed speed away from the start and assumed command in the early going, drifted to the three path into the first turn and floated out a pair of rivals, set moderate fractions while prompted through the backstretch run, led the way into the far turn while under pressure, drifted out to the three path nearing the top of the lane, was overtaken into the stretch, chased to the furlong grounds and faded in the late stages. DESERT RUMBLE was forwardly placed away from the start, raced outside of rivals into the first turn and was floated five wide leaving the seven-furlong marker, stalked the moderate pace from the outside through the backstretch run, gained ground three wide heading to the quarter marker, was floated out into the lane and came four wide for the stretch drive, could not keep pace into deep stretch and tired. CATTIN ALL AROUND was forwardly placed leaving the break, was floated to the four path entering the first turn but recovered and attended to the pace into the backstretch run, stalked VHAGAR through moderate fractions to the half-mile pole, pressed that rival to the quarter marker, could not keep pace into the stretch and gave way.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 6F All Weather Track CR: 84. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DRIVER'S ED came away well from the gate and was hustled to the front, then once clear was put under some restraint, was pressed early and through the turn by BAILS HIM OUT, had something in reserve when that foe moved to challenge at the top of the stretch, held sway then widened in deep stretch, easily holding off a late challenge to the outside near the line. CHIPPEWA BUD was not pressed for speed from the start, settled near the rear of the compact field and remained there as the field headed into the turn, was asked to go on past the three furlong marker, stayed towards the inside on the turn for home, got a nice hole to run through near the furlong pole, tipped out a path and responded to intermittent urging with a late surge to grab the second spot. BAILS HIM OUT broke in and bothered GORM after the break, then got forwardly placed and took up a stalking position right behind DRIVER'S ED, followed that into the turn then moved up to challenge with some confidence, pulled even at the top of the stretch but had trouble changing leads, could not reel in that foe and was passed late for the place. LASMUIGH (GB) came away in good order and raced in the middle of the tightly bunched pack through the early stages, made a forward move through the turn while three wide, came into the stretch with every chance then struggled to keep up in final furlong. GORM broke a step slow then got squeezed after the break, had to steady and was slow to get going, recovered nicely and was in the mix before passing the five furlong marker, tracked the top two through the turn then quickened along with LASMUIGH (GB) from about the five-sixteenths but soon had to idle behind horses turning into the stretch, briefly had a hole to run through along the rail but could not take advantage and finished one-paced down the stretch. TALISKER BAY did not show speed from the start, raced wide and near the back of the field down the backstretch, continued to trail the field through the turn, angled out five wide into the stretch and could do no better than chase the field to the wire.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 6F All Weather Track CR: 63. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $22,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BETTOR BET'R settled just off of the early pace and was well positioned in the opening stages, tracked the decent pace two then three wide to the quarter marker, maintained a three wide path into the stretch and made a mild gain at the furlong marker, closed determinedly into the final sixteenth, surged in deep stretch, caught SHADOWED THOUGHTS in the final strides and got up on the wire to prevail. SHADOWED THOUGHTS was bumped at the start but was away in good order and was prominent in the early running, contested the decent early pace outside of PONDERGATING then assumed command into the turn, set a moderate pace to the quarter marker and drew to a clear lead into the stretch, was kept to task while clear into the final sixteenth, was all out to hold off oncoming rivals in deep stretch, was tagged on the wire for the win and just held for the place. BROOKYS GAL was prominent leaving the start, took back and tracked the decent early pace from the inside, lost ground along the turn and chased two wide to the quarter pole, came in tight and waited for racing room in upper stretch, shifted four wide at the furlong grounds, closed fast into the final sixteenth, surged in the final strides and just missed for the win and place, while well clear of the rest for the show. STREET TIGER broke out at the start and was away a bit slowly, tracked the decent early pace from the outside, gained ground four wide approaching the quarter pole, maintained that four wide path into the stretch, shifted five wide at mid-stretch and lost ground nearing the furlong marker, lacked the needed response in the final sixteenth and finished evenly. BABY I'M A STAR was allowed to settle away from the start, tracked the decent early pace two wide into the turn and chased to the quarter pole, swung six wide into upper stretch, responded to urging inside of the furlong marker and improved position in deep stretch. PONDERGATING broke out at the start but was away in good order and pressed the decent early pace from the inside, lost position into the turn and chased to the quarter pole, ran evenly while in pursuit to mid-stretch and faded in the final stages. SYGRAYEM bobbled leaving the start and was off a step slowly, rushed up in the early stages and raced close to the decent early pace, stalked three then two wide into the turn and raced within aim at the quarter pole, lost ground into the stretch and chased to the furlong marker, lacked a late response and tired. CHAMAVILLE lost her path at the start and was away slowly, chased the early pace from the rear, saved ground along the turn and did not factor in the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Shadowed Thoughts
ENTRY.OWNER: Daehling Farms LLC and Tavares Norman

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 4 6F All Weather Track CR: 68. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: I'M GONNA SHINE got a good break but was not involved in the early pace down the backstretch, raced at the head of the tracking group to the turn, idled in traffic near the three-furlong pole while surrounded by horses, found a hole near the rail at the three-sixteenths marker, responded to a vigorous hand ride surged between horses and prevailed. SELSAE outrun from the break, settled well off the pace, launched a bid from the three furlong pole but had to work through traffic, got clear near the three sixteenths pole, swung five wide into clear and produced a bold rally down the stretch to just miss. HARBOR DEAREST was quick away from the gate and pulled the rider towards the lead, was taken firmly in hand and kept a couple of lengths behind HEAVENLY VIOLET, was let loose at the three furlong marker, pulled even at the quarter pole, then set down at the top of the stretch and battled gamely to the wire only to come up short. VALERIE broke well but ceded the lead, choosing to track the pacesetter from a few lengths back, started a forward move from the three furlong pole, pulled even three wide turning for home then ran on well but flattened a bit late and was passed for a minor award. HARBOR'S BEAUTY was bumped by ZEE PERFECT RUN at the break and in turn bumped into JUST SERENE, had to regroup and lagged behind for the backstretch run, made an extended bid through the turn to get into striking position, lugged in a bit at the top of the stretch and ended up looking for running room while behind a wall of horses, was kept to task and gained late. JUST SERENE bumped hard by HARBOR'S BEAUTY at the break and was away last, chased the pack from far behind, tried to make up some ground through the turn but was forced to travel three to four wide, came into the stretch about five wide kept grinding away and managed to improve a couple of positions. ZEE PERFECT RUN veered out sharply at the start, pushing HARBOR'S BEAUTY into JUST SERENE, took up then was forced to chased from the back of the field through the turn, kept to task down the stretch and was gaining some in the late stages. REALLY SATISFYING got away well then was allowed to find a comfortable rhythm through the early going, moved up into contention on the turn while saving ground along the rail, was still with a chance near the eighth pole but could not keep up in the final furlong. HEAVENLY VIOLET broke sharply from the outside, moved over to the rail when clear, came under pressure passing the quarter pole and faded down the stretch.

FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE OCTOBER 1 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Claiming And Starter Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUPERSONIC FLYER showed speed leaving the start and assumed command in the early going, set a fast pace into the turn and showed the way to the quarter marker while prompted by MAYCEE JO, kicked to a clear lead into upper stretch, was kept to task while clear into the final sixteenth, felt late pressure from TURA LURA, was fully extended in the final strides and lasted for the win at the finish. TURA LURA was forwardly placed leaving the start and tracked the fast early pace, chased two wide into the turn and gained ground at the quarter marker, tipped three wide into the stretch and chased SUPERSONIC FLYER to the furlong grounds, responded to urging into the final sixteenth, rallied in deep stretch, pressured the winner in the final strides, just missed for the win on the wire and was clear in the end for second. GET'EM TIGER tracked the fast early pace from the second flight, chased two wide and between runners heading to the quarter marker, slipped to the rail into upper stretch and made a mild gain at the furlong marker, closed willingly into the final sixteenth, was outkicked by the top two in deep stretch and outfinished CODE RIBBON in the final strides to secure third. CODE RIBBON was squeezed leaving the start and took up at the break, regrouped and was allowed to settle in the early running, raced two wide into the turn, angled three wide at the quarter marker, was guided four wide into the stretch and improved position at the furlong marker, drifted out in the final furlong but was gaining in deep stretch and missed for the show honors. MAYCEE JO showed early speed and was prominent away from the start, stalked the fast pace into the turn and kept close attendance to SUPERSONIC FLYER heading to the quarter marker, lost ground into the stretch and chased SUPERSONIC FLYER to the furlong marker, could not muster a late response and weakened. SHOUT IT OUT chased the fast early pace outside of rivals, raced three wide to the quarter marker, came four wide into the stretch and finished evenly. LADY IN A HURRY was unhurried leaving the start, saved ground into the turn, tipped to the two path into upper stretch and offered a mild late rally. SHELBY GOLD chased the fast early pace while between runners, lost ground into the turn and raced two wide to the quarter pole, came three wide into the stretch and did not factor. RUNNING LUCK chased the fast early pace from the inside, dropped back nearing the top of the lane and tired in the stretch drive.

Claiming Price $62,500 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $50,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAM'S LITTLE ANGEL showed speed leaving the start and was prominent in the opening stages, ceded the early lead to NAUGHTY NADINE and tracked the fast pace through the backstretch run, raced three wide into the far turn and loomed nearing the quarter pole, took command into upper stretch and drove to a clear lead at the furlong marker, drew off into the final sixteenth and was ridden out to the finish to be much the best. SIGNORINA MERISI (GB) rated off of the fast early pace and tracked three wide into the first turn, maintained that three wide path into the backstretch run and tracked the fast pace approaching the half-mile marker, made a mild gain three wide at the quarter pole and continued to advance at mid-stretch, was outkicked inside of the furlong pole, was no match for the winner in the final sixteenth and ran on to be second best. ASSIGNATION was allowed to settle leaving the start, saved ground into the first turn then was guided to the two path into the backstretch run, was unhurried through the first half-mile, saved ground into the far turn and advanced heading to the quarter pole, tipped two wide for the drive and continued to gain ground heading to mid-stretch, split rivals at the furlong pole, could not match strides with the top pair in the late stages and ran on in the final sixteenth to be clear for third. ARINA (GER) took back off of the fast early pace, settled two wide into the first turn then was guided three wide for the backstretch run, raced two wide into the far turn, swung to the three path into the stretch and gained ground at the furlong marker, lacked the needed response in deep stretch and was outfinished for third in the final sixteenth. CLOCKSTRIKESTWELVE was squeezed by neighboring rivals at the start and was away a bit slowly, was unhurried in the early going and saved ground into the first turn, saved all of the ground while settling through the backstretch run, swung to the four path into the stretch and passed tired rivals in the late stages. ZAZEN forwardly placed leaving the start, was keen and pulled on the rider along the first turn, engaged with NAUGHTY NADINE into the backstretch run and pressed the pacesetter through fast fractions, kept close attendance to NAUGHTY NADINE into the far turn, lost position into the stretch and chased to the furlong grounds, could not keep pace into deep stretch and tired. NAUGHTY NADINE (GB) showed speed away from the start, vied for the early lead with TAM'S LITTLE ANGEL then assumed command into the first turn, was engaged by ZAZEN entering the backstretch run and was pressed by that rival while carving fast fractions to the half-mile marker, continued to be hounded by ZAZEN into the far turn, was overtaken by TAM'S LITTLE ANGEL into upper stretch, chased to the furlong grounds and gave way in deep stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 7 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 104. Allowance Purse 31000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won The Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AUSPICIOUS STYLE tracked the early pace from the second flight, raced three wide into the backstretch run and tracked outside of rivals approaching the half-mile marker, was well placed heading to the far turn and was roused three then four wide approaching the quarter pole, swung to the five path into upper stretch, loomed at the furlong marker, battled with STONE'S RIVER into the final sixteenth, bested that game rival in deep stretch and edged away in the final strides to prevail. STONE'S RIVER was prominent leaving the start and vied for the lead into the first turn, assumed command and set the pace into the backstretch run, was well handled through decent fractions approaching the half-mile pole, showed the way to the quarter marker while in hand, drifted to the two path into upper stretch and kept to task to the furlong grounds, met the bid of AUSPICIOUS STYLE into the final sixteenth, was gamely bested by the winner in deep stretch and held safely in the end for second. ENOS SLAUGHTER was allowed to settle leaving the break, tucked in to the rail and saved ground along the first turn, settled through the backstretch run while not far back, came in tight into the far turn and was blocked nearing the quarter pole, continued to race in traffic into upper stretch, gained ground nearing mid-stretch and swung six wide at the furlong marker, needed more in the final sixteenth and outfinished PHOSPHORESCENCE in deep stretch to secure third. PHOSPHORESCENCE (FR) was squeezed at the start but was away in good order, rated off of the early pace and tracked from the second flight, raced two wide and between runners into the backstretch run, maintained that position heading to the half-mile marker, came in tight while between and two wide approaching the quarter pole, slipped to the inside into upper stretch and gained ground at the furlong marker, was outkicked into the final sixteenth and was edged for third in the final strides. MOTHER'S PRAYER was forwardly placed away from the start and tracked the early pace, raced three wide along the first turn and was well placed into the backstretch run, tracked the decent pace to the half-mile marker, gained ground three wide at the quarter pole, swung to the four path into the stretch, continued to advance into the drive and came within range at the furlong pole, could not sustain his run into deep stretch and weakened. ONE FAST BRO was unhurried away from the start, lagged through the backstretch run, saved ground into the far turn while trailing, swung to the four path into the stretch and did not threaten. EL ALTO HOMBRE showed speed away from the start and vied for the early lead, took back and stalked the pace into the first turn, maintained a two wide path into the backstretch run and stalked the decent fractions to the half-mile marker, advanced two wide heading to the quarter pole, came three wide into the stretch, chased to the furlong grounds and faded in the late stages. DESHAMBEAU was forwardly placed away from the start and saved ground into the first turn, stalked the decent pace through the backstretch run, saved all of the ground into the far turn, lost postilion at the quarter pole, dropped back into the stretch and tired in the final furlong.

ENTRY.COMMENT: sent,well handled,met late bid,gamely bested,held safe 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Oakland S. GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 6F All Weather Track CR: 106. Stakes Purse 50000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. No Nomination Fee. $50 to enter with $50,000 Added. $100 supplementary nominations may be made at time of entry. Weights: Three Year Olds, 122 lbs; Older 124 lbs. Highest earnings preferred. Closed Wednesday, November 8, 2 023 with 18 nominations. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAR RACER was away in good order and was prominent leaving the start, raced close up to the fast early pace and stalked four wide into the turn, lost a bit of ground into the turn and chased four wide to the quarter marker, loomed five wide into upper stretch and vied for the lead at the furlong marker, took command nearing the sixteenth-pole, dug in into deep stretch and drew away in the final stages to prevail. RAGER settled off the fast early pace and tracked outside of runners into the turn, gained ground five wide approaching the quarter marker, swung seven wide for the stretch drive and continued his sustained rally at mid-stretch, could not match strides with STAR RACER into the final sixteenth and outfinished the rest to earn place honors. TOP HARBOR took back leaving the start and tracked the fast early pace while between runners, raced four wide into the turn and swung six wide for the stretch drive, loomed at the furlong marker, raced in tight quarters into the final sixteenth, was outkicked in deep stretch and determinedly stayed on in the final strides to secure third at the wire. UNRAPTURED was hustled leaving the start and assumed command in the early going, contested the fast pace three wide approaching the half-mile marker, lost ground into the turn and chased the leading pair to the quarter pole, swung to the four path into the stretch and re-bid at the furlong marker, battled into the final sixteenth, needed more in deep stretch and was just edged for third at the wire. ROBIE was prominent leaving the start and pressed the fast early pace between rivals, disputed the quick pace into the turn and vied for the lead at the quarter pole, battled into the stretch, could not match strides with oncoming rivals into the final furlong and weakened. ALEXANDER'S DREAM was forwardly placed leaving the start, came in tight at the five-furlong marker and was shuffled back approaching the half-mile pole, recovered and chased the fast pace from the inside heading into the turn, saved ground to the quarter marker, tipped two wide into the stretch and rallied nearing the furlong marker, vied for the lead at mid-stretch, could not keep pace into the final sixteenth and gave way in deep stretch. TALBOT BAY took back off of the fast early pace, tracked the leaders from a two wide position heading to the turn, raced between rivals into the turn and steadied midway through the bend, angled to the four path into the stretch and re-bid approaching the furlong grounds, lacked the needed response in the final sixteenth and was outkicked. LOVE CANDY was asked for speed leaving the start and was sent to contest the early pace, disputed the fast pace into the turn and carved out quick fractions heading to the quarter marker, lost position into the stretch, chased to the furlong marker and faded in the final stages.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 9 6F All Weather Track CR: 94. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE OCTOBER 1 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY DOMINATOR broke sharply but backed away from the developing three-way speed duel, moved closer while holding the rail when that trio split up passing the half mile pole, waited for room through the turn, slipped through the inside path when RALLY CAT left the rail open at the head of the stretch, sprinted away from the rest and won geared down. MY DAD IS THIRSTY bumped twice with R M C HOOK'EM after the start, then rushed up to be part of a three-horse pace duel then was three wide and fell back a bit on the turn as RALLY CAT quickened away, re-bid and was in the middle of a five-horse fan into the stretch, kept to task down the stretch and outfinished all but the winner. RALLY CAT broke best and seized the lead from the gate, was soon joined by ROISTER to the inside and MY DAD IS THIRSTY to the outside, slipped away from that pair passing the half-mile marker, tried to put some distance on the field from the five-sixteenths pole but became surrounded by challenges at the top of the stretch, still held the lead, battled gamely and held off all but the eventual winner to mid-stretch only to lose the place in the final yards. R M C HOOK'EM exchanged bumps with MY DAD IS THIRSTY after the break, remained to the outside in the clear through the early stages, made a five wide sweeping move through the turn, came into the stretch on the outside of five horses bidding to take command in the stretch, finished up well but did not have another gear when called upon. DEALERS HAND was content to track behind the pace duel down the backstretch, then became stuck behind horses through the turn, angled out to the five path for the stretch run but could not produce the needed response. ROISTER got away well then rushed up to race between a trio contesting the early pace, did not respond when RALLY CAT quickened near the half mile pole, attempted to re-engage approaching the quarter pole, was in good position turning into the stretch but weakened in the final furlong. HARBOR SKY rider lost the right iron right after the break, struggled for control then intentionally slipped out the left iron passing the half mile pole, opting to ride bareback the rest of the way, swung six wide into the stretch, kept to task with a steady hand ride and managed to out-finish one. CONTINENTAL UNION was away a bit slowly then under pressure to keep pace through the early going, raced four to five wide through the turn the swung out to the seven path for the stretch run and flattened out.
